# EAS Build ignore file — monorepo root.
#
# EAS Build detects this pnpm workspace and uploads the entire
# monorepo so the mobile app's workspace dependencies resolve.
# That means `.easignore` needs to live here, at the monorepo
# root, not just under `apps/leadsmart-mobile/`. Patterns below
# are excluded from the tar shipped to Expo's build workers.
#
# Root cause for this file existing: Android build
# 2d6af698-bf27-4bd9-9a7c-34f630ed9bc3 errored in the
# PREPARE_PROJECT phase because tar tried to archive
# `.claude/worktrees/` — the parent of sibling git worktrees
# managed by Claude Code sessions — and those worktrees
# reference files that don't exist in the current checkout's
# index, producing thousands of "Cannot open: No such file or
# directory" errors. `.claude/` has no business in a production
# bundle regardless.

# Claude Code local working directory (worktrees, sessions, logs)
.claude/

# Scratch / caches
**/.turbo/
**/.next/
apps/propertytoolsai/tmp/
apps/propertytoolsai/ml/valuation/artifacts/
apps/leadsmart-mobile/dist/

# Local env + secrets
.env
.env.*.local
**/.env
**/.env.*.local

# Large asset source archives
*.zip
*.tar.gz
